development shall be allocated to the Alabama Department of
HB236 Engrossed
234 Education to be distributed to the Ed Farm Classroom of
235 Tomorrow. These funds will be used by Ed Farm to provide
236 technology tools and professional development services to
237 classroom teachers in an effort to improve instruction and
238 student learning gains. It is the intent of the legislature
239 that in addition to general programmatic costs, Ed Farm may
240 also expend funds for software, hardware, administrative
241 costs, and professional learning services.
242 (2) The State Superintendent shall provide a report of the
243 initiative to the Chair of the House Ways and Means-Education
244 Committee and the Chair of the Senate Committee on Finance and
245 Taxation-Education no later than October 1, 2027.
