292 Section 4. (a) Notwithstanding the provisions of Section
293 29-9-4, Code of Alabama 1975, and in addition to all other
294 appropriations heretofore or hereafter made, there is hereby
295 appropriated a total of $150,000,000 from the Education Trust
296 Fund Advancement and Technology Fund to the Department of
297 Education to provide matching grants to local education
298 agencies for expenses related to developing regional career
299 technology centers throughout the state, including capital
300 outlay and equipment, for the fiscal year ending September 30,
301 2026. Grant proposals shall be submitted by a collaboration of
302 at lease two local education agencies or between a local
303 education agency partnering with a community college within
304 the Alabama Community College System. Should a local education
305 agency partner with a community college, the local education
Page 12

agency partner with a community college, the local education
HB236 Engrossed
306 agency shall maintain full control of the grant from the
307 Department of Education. The State Superintendent of Education
308 shall utilize a sliding scale of matching requirements for
309 grant proposals, taking into consideration the financial
310 capacity of the eligible local education agencies to provide
311 matching funds, so long as the required match does not exceed
312 50 percent of the total cost of the project. The State
313 Superintendent of Education shall give priority in awarding
314 grants pursuant to this section to grant proposals from local
315 education agencies that were not awarded to full amount of
316 grant funds requested pursuant to Act 2025-269, and to grant
317 proposals from local education agencies that submitted
318 applications for grant funds pursuant Act 2025-269 but did not
319 receive a grant.
320 (b) The State Superintendent of Education shall notify
321 each local superintendent and finance officer of each local
322 education agency by email regarding the availability and
323 application process of grants to be awarded pursuant to this
324 section, including any required forms. The State
325 Superintendent shall notify all members of the local
326 legislative delegation five days prior to the announcement of
327 any grant made to any entity located in the legislative
328 jurisdiction. The five days prior notice requirement shall be
329 waived in the event of a declared emergency. The Governor
Page 13

waived in the event of a declared emergency. The Governor
HB236 Engrossed
330 shall encourage the Department to disburse the funds provided
331 herein on a nondiscriminatory basis.
332 Section 5. All funds appropriated herein and not
333 expended in the current fiscal year shall not revert but be
334 carried forward for the purpose appropriated.
335 Section 6. This act shall become effective immediately
336 following its passage and approval by the Governor, or its
337 otherwise becoming law.
